Fresh and balanced tacos. Had simple vegetarian/vegan (rice, beans, pico de gallo) on corn tacos with their red and green sauces-- this is addiction. Haha thank goodness they deliver if you need a fix. Everyone including the owners work day and night to keep this truck running with quality and consistency. I was able to meet the owners and learn that they are two love birds who met while working at a thai restaurant in brooklyn/church ave (so sweet!)--she was from Thailand and he was from Mexico. And though they had their language barrier, and came with very little to this country, they worked really hard and eventually began this food truck. They now operate this delicious business, employ many, and feed us! Really some of the most inspiring people I've met. Before I get too soppy, anywho, THESE hot sauces....wish I could buy a bucket full, they are so good and fresh!

My favorite spot when I'm back in Brooklyn. Fair prices and very nice employees. They can be a bit delayed when getting a few customers, but it's understandable. Be patient and the food is worth it! Bundle up in cold weather, as you're waiting outside, but on a nice spring day, the wait isn't bad. A Chase bank is conveniently located right next to the truck, in case you don't have cash on you. Right across from a Starbucks in case you need somewhere to eat with friends.  Overall, one of my favorite places to get food!
